| `-e ENVIRONMENT`, `--environment ENVIRONMENT` | If the configuration contains multiple [environments](../configuration.md#environmentname-block), specify the ENVIRONMENT that should be used (e.g. production). The host(s) and settings can be different per environment. |
| `-s NAME=VALUE`, `--setting NAME=VALUE` | Override the setting NAME with the given VALUE. Refer to the [settings overrides](../configuration.md#overrides) documentation for a detailed explanation. |
| `--[no-]dry-run` | Simulate running tasks instead of using real SSH. |
